column5: Got up to the Bay of Quinte for our yearly trip.        We caught most of our fish on stick baits trolling.
Well done.  I could not get up that way this year due to work.  Nice to see people out catching fish in cold weather.  Nothing beats it.
Jeez, brave holding the lure like that in the last pic   Nice fish, looks dang cold!!!  Joey
Awesome fish!!! Looks cold but well worth it for the fish caught
snow doesn't stop them critters !!! Nice eyes !!! oh and the fish are nice too.
Tell Steve a bellaclava and shades don't hide his identity! LOL  Some decent fish on a blustery day..
Nice job guys! I ran a "Power Dive" when we were at the GTG, but no action for us. Nice to see yah Steve, sure do wish you still stayed active here! Regards... HH
He sure knows how to fish.  One of the better trips I've had with him.  He has a lot more pictures of the trip.
Steve is definetely the master of BIG Quinte pickeral in the fall.  Some nice fish there boys.
nice going got to love BOQ
You will definitely be breaking ice Saturday Dave
looks cozy warm on the BOQ  Great report!  Some really beauts!  Cheers!
Great job guys. Really beautiful fish. Thanks for sharing your adventure with us.
By the looks of it the only launch that will be free will be the the one near Bath and tthe one at the ferry. Be safe!
Guys were fishing on ice today
